---
description: Gate FeatureFlags with isActiveWindow in app code
globs: src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: true
---

# FeatureFlags usage

In application code (anywhere outside `FeatureFlags.ts` itself), **do not** use a flag constant as a bare boolean (e.g. `if (FeatureFlags.myFlag)`).

Always wrap the flag through **`FeatureFlags.isActiveWindow`** so production builds stay off unless the flag is enabled **and** the code is running on a dev machine (`localhost` / `192.168.*`). SSR uses the `"server"` hostname and treats the window as inactive unless you adjust that logic in `FeatureFlags.ts`.

```typescript
// Bad
if (FeatureFlags.visualQueryBuilder) {
}

// Good
if (FeatureFlags.isActiveWindow(FeatureFlags.visualQueryBuilder)) {
}

// Good — name the result when reused
const visualQueryBuilderUi = FeatureFlags.isActiveWindow(
  FeatureFlags.visualQueryBuilder,
);
```

**Exception:** Inside `FeatureFlags.ts`, defining `isActiveWindow` or the flag constants does not use this pattern on those same reads.
